        <title locale="en_US">&lt;i&gt;Pseudasthenes&lt;/i&gt;, a new genus of ovenbird (Aves: Passeriformes: Furnariidae) </title>
        <abstract locale="en_US">Phylogenetic analysis of the family Furnariidae (Aves: Passeriformes) indicates that the genus &lt;i&gt;Asthenes&lt;/i&gt; is polyphyletic, consisting of two groups that are not sister taxa. &lt;i&gt;Pseudasthenes,&lt;/i&gt; a new genus of ovenbird, is described for one of these groups. The four species included in the new genus, formerly placed in &lt;i&gt;Asthenes,&lt;/i&gt; are &lt;i&gt;P.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;humicola,&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;P.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;patagonica,&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;P.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;steinbachi,&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;P.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;cactorum.&lt;/i&gt;</abstract>
